    "body": "I did first attempt and it seems very hard: \r\n- our logger does escaping by default, in result log looks like: \r\n```\r\nTRACE[09-09|12:20:27.473] Served                                   conn=127.0.0.1:56320 method=eth_syncing t=1.395385ms request=\"{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"id\\\":1,\\\"method\\\":\\\"eth_syncing\\\",\\\"params\\\":[]}\" response=\"{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"id\\\":1,\\\"result\\\":{\\\"currentBlock\\\":\\\"0x0\\\",\\\"highestBlock\\\":\\\"0xa52f61\\\"}}\"\r\n```\r\n- also now we have no way in code to get current verbosity - it means logging must have no performance penalty\r\n- also now request parsing is separated from response serialization\r\n\r\n\r\nI wonder if instead of using logs, we can use something similar to Nginx - separated file called `access.log` - where we maybe will write more than just request/response, but also user-agent and maybe some http headers. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
